race.comment: ZARKANA (4) resumes and while she hasn't won for some time, she clearly has ability. Horror draws left her with too much to do last prep, but she gets the chance to settle closer here. The trip may be short of her best, yet her lead-up work suggests she can fire fresh. TRANTORO (7) has mixed her form this campaign but boasts a strong record over this track and trip. The wide gate is a challenge, though her peaks measure up and she can give this a shake. ROB THE BANK (1) was a determined winner here fresh before failing in town last start. Back to a winning track and reunited with Murtagh, he can bounce back sharply. ARTFUL TAWNY (2) was plain first-up after a long break but should have tightened up and can show much more this time. BOLTED IN (5) is a proven three-time winner at the journey and gets in well with the claim. Worth keeping safe.
